			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=3>
				[[[It would be a place to be in peace if you choose, to remain in your home town and make a living off of tailoring. ]]] <br>  <br> I wish they would let that work. =( I sooo wanted to be a tailor and nothing but a tailor, but when you start the game broke, you need to hunt for some money. Well, ya hunt for that then you buy the sewing kit. Then you hunt more to get patterns. Then you need to kill the animals for the pelts. So, finally you start to make stuff. Well, very few players want to buy it and sells back to the merchants for a horrible cost. And you are forced to keep hunting and killing more than tailoring just to keep enough money to work on the skill. <br>  <br> Jewelcraft. I have a high elf enchanter that is a jeweler (currently have 65 in it! woohoo!) and has lost a good 700plat just getting to where he is now in the skill. I can see some money loss, but when you create a ring, jade for example, and pay six gold for the bar and four plat for the gem, then enchant the bar and make the ring. Well, the merchants think those +5hp and mana rings are pretty much as useful as the gem itself, because the only give you the cost of the gem plus a couple silver back when selling to them. *sigh* I doubt they'll ever do anything for us roleplayers. They haven't yet, so why would they now? <br>  <br> -Dret Delurthan <br> Halfing Rogue of Xegony <br> Proud member of The Doom Guild		

